ActPreclearance Act, 2016
SubjectOrder Designating Certain Members of the Queen's Privy Council for Canada to be Minister for the Purposes of this Act and Certain Sections of that Act in Certain Circumstances: (1) the Minister of Public Safety and Emergency Preparedness; (2) the Minister of Transport; and (3) the Minister of Foreign Affairs
PrecisOrder (1) designating the Minister of Public Safety and Emergency Preparedness, a member of the Queen's Privy Council for Canada as the responsible Minister for the purposes of the PRECLEARANCE ACT, 2016; (2) designating the Minister of Public Safety and Emergency Preparedness, a member of the Queen's Privy Council for Canada, as the Minister for the purposes of sections 6 to 8 of the PRECLEARANCE ACT, 2016 in circumstances concerning highways, roads, bridges, tunnels and paths, (3) designating the Minister of Transport, a member of the Queen's Privy Council for Canada, as the Minister for the purposes of sections 6 to 8 of the PRECLEARANCE ACT, 2016 in circumstances and railways and railway terminals; and (4) designating the Minister of Foreign Affairs, a member of the Queen's Privy Council for Canada, as the minister for the purposes of section 41 of the PRECLEARANCE ACT, 2016.
